# Running Tests

This project uses [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/) with a committed `uv.lock`. Always run tests through `uv run`:

```powershell
# Correct — uv resolves the locked env automatically (no activation needed)
uv run pytest tests/ -v

# Run a specific test file
uv run pytest tests/test_config.py -v
```

If the environment is missing or out of sync, create it from the lockfile first:

```powershell
uv sync --frozen --extra dev
```

Do NOT run bare `python -m pytest` or `pytest` — the system Python does not have project dependencies installed.

Do NOT run `pip install` to fix missing dependencies, and do NOT hand-edit `uv.lock` — use `uv sync` (and `uv lock` when dependencies change).

# Shell Environment

This project runs on Windows with PowerShell. Avoid bash-only commands:
- Use `Select-Object -First N` instead of `head -N`
- Use `Select-Object -Last N` instead of `tail -N`
- Use `Select-String` instead of `grep` (or use `rg` which is available)
